snippet: There has been a lot of tinkering with financial regulation, bringing incremental progress, but more could be done for the banking industry to serve the good of the economy.
abstract: Jesse Eisinger The Trade column assesses the efficacy of Dodd-Frank financial reform legislation and degree to which it has made financial sector safer; suggests that while incremental reform has occurred, more needs to be done to make finance help nation's economy; questions likelihood of more reform in light of fact that Citigroup has succeeded in getting legislation it drafted passed.
lead_paragraph: There has been a lot of tinkering with financial regulation, bringing incremental progress, but more could be done for the banking industry to serve the good of the economy.

headline.print_headline: Despite Changes, an Overhaul of Wall Street Falls Short
